==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hoiden
<hw>Hoi"den</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>hoydon</ets>
a lout, rustic, OD. <ets>heyden</ets> a heathen, gypsy, vagabond, D.
<ets>heiden</ets>, fr. OD. <ets>heyde</ets> heath, D. <ets>heide</ets>.
See <er>Heathen</er>, <er>Heath</er>.]</ety> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>hoyden</asp>.]</altsp> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A rude, clownish
youth.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A rude, bold girl; a romp.</def> <rj><au>H.
Kingsley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hoiden</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hoiden
<hw>Hoi"den</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Rustic; rude; bold.</def>
<rj><au>Younq.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hoiden</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Hoiden
<hw>Hoi"den</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To romp rudely or
indecently.</def> <rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hoidenhood</ent>⟦br⟧
